"Brown adipose tissue has low levels of uncoupling protein 1","White adipocytes contain multiple small lipid droplets","White adipose tissue generates significant heat"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBrown adipose tissue has a high density of mitochondria\u003C/strong\u003E throughout the cytoplasm. These numerous mitochondria contain uncoupling protein 1 (UCP1), which uncouples oxidative phosphorylation from ATP production to generate heat.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBrown adipose tissue contains a single large lipid droplet\u003C/strong\u003E - Brown adipocytes contain multiple small lipid droplets, unlike white adipocytes which have a single large droplet\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBrown adipose tissue has low levels of uncoupling protein 1\u003C/strong\u003E - High UCP1 expression is characteristic of brown adipose tissue and essential for its thermogenic function\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWhite adipocytes contain multiple small lipid droplets\u003C/strong\u003E - White adipocytes have a single large lipid droplet that occupies most of the cell volume\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWhite adipose tissue generates significant heat\u003C/strong\u003E - White adipose tissue primarily stores energy and provides insulation, while brown adipose tissue is specialised for heat generation\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe high mitochondrial density in brown adipose tissue, combined with UCP1 expression, enables its primary function of non-shivering thermogenesis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["White adipose tissue stores energy in the form of a single large lipid droplet and has few mitochondria.","Brown adipose tissue contains numerous mitochondria and multiple small lipid droplets.","Uncoupling protein 1 (UCP1) in brown 